Level 148: You see all of the fan fiction writers chained up behind desks with someone with a shirt labeled "fanbase" whipping them to "motivate" them.
Floor 149: The break floor, with shelves upon shelves of Brain Bleach
Floor 150: A never ending dark corridor with this bumping around.
Floor 151: Another floor with a spotlight on a single bottle of Brain Bleach as an apology for last floor
Floor 152:
Floor 153: The secure connection to floor 154 will arrive once every 24 hours.
Floor 154: What is it that's not exactly water and it ain't exactly earth?
Floor 155: Ropes 1" out of reach of floor 154 victims.
One-Hundred and Fifty-Six floors above groundlevel:
Floor 167: Random quantum wormholes, signs all saying this is the one to the next floor.
Floor 168: There lives a man, whom you don't know. He comes to you and tells you
Floor 169: A bunch of middle/high schoolers laughing hard, no reason seems apparent.
Foor 170: Brian Greene knitting furiously
Floor 171: PALINDROMES EVERYWHERE!! !RACECAR!

Floor 173: A room with the KSP servers.
Floor 174: The US and Russia on a monopoly board showing everything they are doing during the 1940's through the 2000's
Floor 175: A dollar and 75 cants are lying on the floor.
Floor 176: Pure binary, 1s and 0s, all floating around, mingling, making random numbers... It's mesmerizing, but you move on.

Floor 177: Several chrome canisters about a meter and a half high and half a meter wide, all perfectly set in rows. Each canister has a different number and name printed on the front. The most apparent ones are 095, 096, 097 and "Catalyst", "Clockwork", and "Rage"

Floor 179: You read a sign and it says:

Dear friend, you've skipped floor 178. Keep going and to explore SPACE! --- Jeb
Floor 180: You see a random enemy rocket that gets destroyed by agent Kirrim
Floor 181: The place where all the socks end up that vanish while doing laundry
Floor 182: all the people who gave up on trying to find their socks
